Derivative of inverse and singular values #  Derivative of inverse #  Given matrix $ \mathcal{A(t)} $, how does it relate to $ \mathcal{ A^{-1}(t) } $, in detail:
 Given $  rac{d(A)}{dt} $, find $  rac{d(A^{-1})}{dt} $  Let start with,
$ B^{-1} - A^{-1} = B^{-1}(A - B)A^{-1} $
Which mean $ B^{-1} - A^{-1} $ and $ A - B $ has the same rank (because $ B^{-1}, A^{-1}, A, B $ is invertible (has full rank)). Pick $ B = A + 
abla A $, we have
$$  egin{align} &amp; (A + 
abla A)^{-1} - A = (A + 
abla A)^{-1}(A - B)A^{-1} 
ewline \leftrightarrow \quad &amp;  rac{
abla A^{-1}}{
abla t} = -(A + 
abla A)^{-1}( rac{
abla A}{
abla t})A^{-1} \end{align} $$
And as $ 
abla t 	o 0 $, we have:
$  egin{align} &amp; \lim_{
abla t 	o 0 \leftrightarrow 
abla A 	o 0 }  rac{
abla A^{-1}}{
abla t} = \lim_{
abla t 	o 0 \leftrightarrow 
abla A 	o 0 } - (A + 
abla A)^{-1}( rac{
abla A}{
abla t})A^{-1} \
\leftrightarrow \quad &amp; \lim_{
abla t 	o 0 \leftrightarrow 
abla A 	o 0 }  rac{
abla A^{-1}}{
abla t} = \lim_{
abla t 	o 0} - (A)^{-1}( rac{
abla A}{
abla t})A^{-1} \end{align} $
This is equivalent to definition of derivative:
$$  rac{d A^{-1}}{dt} = - A^{-1} rac{dA}{dt}A^{-1} $$
Derivative of eigenvalue $ \lambda $ #  Given eigenvector $ x(t) $ and eigenvalue $ \lambda (t) $:
   Form Left Right     vector $ y^TA = \lambda y^T $ $ Ax = \lambda x $   matrix $ Y^TA = \Lambda Y^T $ $ AX = X\Lambda $    Also $ \mathcal{ Y^TX = I } $, using those formula with a function of $ t $ we have:
$$  egin{align} &amp; y^T(t) A(t) x(t) = \lambda (t) y^T(t) x(t) 
ewline \leftrightarrow \quad &amp; \lambda (t) = y^T(t) A(t) x(t) \end{align} $$
So calulate derivative:
$$  egin{align}  rac{d \lambda}{dt} &amp; =  rac{d y^T}{dt} A x(t) + y^T(t)  rac{d A} {dt} x(t) + y^T(t) A(t)  rac{d x}{dt} 
ewline &amp; = ( rac{d y^T}{dt} A x(t) + y^T(t) A(t)  rac{d x}{dt} ) + y^T(t)  rac{d A} {dt} x(t) 
ewline &amp; = \lambda (t) ( rac{d y^T}{dt} x(t) + y^T(t) rac{d x}{dt}) + y^T(t)  rac{d A} {dt} x(t) 
ewline &amp; = 0 + y^T(t)  rac{d A} {dt} x(t) 
ewline &amp; = y^T(t)  rac{d A} {dt} x(t) 
ewline \end{align} $$
